        //- #########################  Kangaroo
        section
          section
            h1 Kangaroo babies

          section
            h2 The problem
            ul
              li.fragment(style="text-align:justify;font-size:20pt") Almost 1 million children die each year due to complications of preterm birth. Many survivors face a lifetime of disability, including learning disabilities and visual and hearing problems.
              li.fragment(style="text-align:justify;font-size:20pt") Hypothermia and Hypoglycaemia are a great risk, also the more premature the baby, the greater the risk of respiratory distress syndrome.
              li.fragment(style="text-align:justify;font-size:20pt") The premature baby is more susceptible to neonatal jaundice.
              li.fragment(style="text-align:justify;font-size:20pt") They are susceptible to infection and to necrotising enteritis.
              li.fragment(style="text-align:justify;font-size:20pt") They are susceptible to intraventricular brain haemorrhage with serious long-term effects.
            
          section    
            img(src="images/the_facts.jpg" alt="example diabetes")

          section
            h2 Fundación Canguro
            p The “Fundación Canguro” or Kangaroo Foundation created in 1994 in Colombia has as the most important goal pursued to continue the evaluation of the KMC(Kangaroo Mother Care) and to facilitate the dissemination and transference of knowledge and technology associated with this technique, to all those who might benefit from it, with the highest possible quality standards.
            
          section  
            div.left
              img(src="images/KMC.jpg" alt="example diabetes")
            div.right(style="text-align:justify;font-size:25pt") Kangaroo mother care: is a method invented for the Doctor Edgar Rey Sanabria where baby is carried by the mother with skin to skin contact 24 hr a day. The baby is held in a strict up-right position, between the mother’s breasts and under her clothes. Mothers are employed as “incubators” and as the main source of food and stimulation.
                          
          section
            h2 The Experts
            img(src="images/experts.jpg" alt="Fundación Canguro experts")
            p Dr. Nathalie Charpak, Pediatrician and maximum exponent of the KMC in the world.
            p Julieta Villegas, Master’s degree in Health Policy, Planning and Financing.

          section
            h2 The Data
            img(src="images/words_data.jpg" alt="avalaible data")

          section
            h2 The Task
            p The goal of our tool was to be able to evaluate the growth process during the first year of life of premature infants and to identify the influence of variables like the mother’s age, education, weight, height or income in the process. 

          section
